name: biomass_only
label: Hello, PSA On-Farm Team. Will you be doing the full Decomp Bag protocol or Biomass Only?

name: bionote
label: To take cover crop biomass on-farm for PSA - You will be distributed barcodes for each of your field sites. 4 barcodes per site.  Barcode example: CCC-1-A-0

name: bionote2
label: This form has enough spaces for 1 Farm: 4 bag Pre-weights.  To continue, you will need 4 Barcodes for 1 farm site attached to 4 Large Paper Bags or Large Sacks. For each farm, complete a new form.

name: bionote3
label: Note about Scales:  This pre-weight should be to at least 1 decimal place (2 is better), using the same scale, or very similar (ie: decimal point accuracy, model, calibration, etc) that you will use to take dry weight of the same bag later on in the process.

name: decomp
label: Is this your first time doing this bag pre-weight protocol?

name: note1
label: You will be distributed barcodes for your field sites.  24 barcodes per site. Barcodes read as follows: SITE-Rep-Row-Timepoint example: CCC-1-A-3

name: note2
label: This  form has enough spaces for 1 Farm: for 24 Decomp bag Pre-weights.  To continue, you will need: 24 Barcodes for 1 farm site, 20 Mesh Bags (1 mm mesh bags 26cm x 60 cm) with metal tags and 4 Large Paper Bags

name: note3
label: All pre-weights include the tags and labels.

name: note4
label: Note about Scales:  This pre-weight should be to at least 1 decimal place (2 is better), using the same scale, or very similar (ie: decimal point accuracy, model, calibration, etc) that you will use for the fresh weight and dry weight of the same bag later on in the process.
